      "content": "It's true that the person you *thought* you were is gone, and that loss is profound. But the shell you see in the mirror is still a living person capable of change, even if it feels impossible right now. You don't have to try to \"fix\" the past version; instead, you can start exploring what a new, authentic self might look like. Small, gentle steps toward self-compassion are the only way forward from this point.",
      "source": "target",
