      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The idea of a \"new self\" is a hopeful fantasy when you're deep in this kind of despair. Instead of focusing on a future that feels impossible, maybe focus only on making the next hour slightly more bearable. Acknowledging the loss is valid, but that doesn't mean you have to accept the slow slide into nothingness. There is a difference between the person who died and the physical being still breathing; that physical being deserves some kindness, even if it’s just quiet acceptance for now.",
      "source": "target",
